laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Laboratory Examination for Proteus Mirabilis and Beta Streptococcus Group B
laboratory_examinations.findings: Proteus Mirabilis and Beta Streptococcus Group B identified; valuestr 8.4 mg/dL within the reference range (8.4 - 10.3 mg/dL).

There is a small right pleural effusion, moderate stable cardiomegaly, moderate hiatal hernia, normal liver morphology, mild pericholecystic hyperemia, fluid-sludge level in the gallbladder with asymmetric gallbladder wall edema; pancreas and kidneys normal; no concerning lesions.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Cysts in the pancreas are mostly new since an unspecified previous date; there may have been a small cystic lesion at the pancreatic head/neck junction previously.
